    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <head>447. Telegram 7065 from <gloss target="#t_JCS_1">JCS</gloss> to <gloss
                        target="#t_CINCLANT_1">CINCLANT</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CINCONAD_1"
                        >CINCONAD</gloss>, and CINCSAC, October 28<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d447fn1">Instruction not to relax alert procedures despite latest
                        Soviet proposal. Top Secret. 1 p. <gloss target="#t_OSD_1">OSD</gloss>,
                        Historical Office, Secretary of Defense, Cable Files, Cuba, Oct. 25–31,
                        1962.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-10-28">October 28, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d447-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d447-1"/>
                <p>Your attention is invited to latest Soviet proposal. The <gloss target="#t_JCS_1"
                        >JCS</gloss> are of the opinion that this may be an insincere proposal to
                    gain time. Hence, there should be no relaxation of alert procedures.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Herbert D. Riley</signed>
                    <affiliation>Vice Admiral, <gloss target="#t_USN_1">USN</gloss>
                        <lb/>Director, Joint Staff</affiliation>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
